

1.  Fill up your name, and other details in indicated places in the 
    mini.tex file.

2.  Type in your document divided into sections , and subsections as required.
    A sample name for the first section is shown. The label allows you to refer 
    to the unit from other parts of the text using \ref{label}.

3.  The bibname.bib file should be modified to contain your references.
    Samples are given in the file. The references are cited using \cite{key}.

4.  Figures can be drawn in xfig or dia/gnuplot and included in the eps format.     Read documentation on latex to  learn how to include eps figures.




    
